The paper deals with discovering subgroups in graphs based on their connectivity structure, which is a common problem in social network analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also introduces a new method for finding interesting subgroups based on an information-theoretic definition of interestingness, which could fall under cs.SD (Data Mining) or cs.DS (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with analyzing patterns in graphs, which could fall under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science).
